    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-15T00:45:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>[, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1894-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1894-03-15T00:00:00-05:45">undated</date>]. (Received
                                April 1, 1894.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>With telegraph down and low water in river, communication with Bluefields
                            uncertain and almost impossible. Government here without late advices.
                            Braida went to Bluefields to report facts of situation. <pb facs="0528" n="478" xml:id="pg_478"/> Have heard nothing from him. British
                            brought Nicaragua soldiers away and disarmed them. By agreement mixed
                            commission of seven governs temporarily. American merchants
                            dissatisfied. British troops on ship. Nicaragua withdrawn exequatur from
                            Braida. Important you send judicious successor immediately.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
